Min Heap (Default)
PriorityQueue<Integer> pq = new PriorityQueue<>();



Max Heap
PriorityQueue<Integer> pq =
    new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());


. Important Methods
Method	Meaning
add(x)	insert element
offer(x)	insert element
peek()	see top element
poll()	remove top element
size()	heap size
isEmpty()	check empty




Heap of Pairs

Very important for:

top k frequent
k closest points
merge k sorted lists

Syntax:

PriorityQueue<int[]> pq =
    new PriorityQueue<>(
        (a,b) -> a[0] - b[0]
    );


Max Heap of Pairs
PriorityQueue<int[]> pq =
    new PriorityQueue<>(
        (a,b) -> b[0] - a[0]
    );
